  "text": "Patient selection. This study was conducted under two Institutional Review Board -approved protocols and all patients signed an informed consent form before treatment. Patients with a histologically or cytologically confirmed diagnosis of malignant solid tumor were eligible for two clinical trials in which patients underwent CYP3A phenotyping with i.v. given midazolam [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Eligibility criteria included age >18 years; performance status V1; and adequate hematopoietic (leukocytes, z4.0 Â 10 9 /L; neutrophils, z1.5 Â 10 9 /L; and platelets, z100 Â 10 9 /L), hepatic (bilirubin within normal limits; transaminases, V2 times the upper limit of normal), and renal function (creatinine clearance, z50 mL/min). All patients were required to have an estimated life expectancy of >12 weeks and no previous chemotherapy was allowed for at least 4 weeks before enrollment. The patients were asked to abstain from substances known to affect the function and/or expression of CYP3A and/or ABCB1 for a period of 2 weeks before, during, and up to 3 weeks after the administration of midazolam.",
